<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <br />
Strategy:<br />
Bid high &#8211; like 5-6 to go first, once your pipe&#8217;s get going you&#8217;ll get rid of all of those pretty easily.<br />
Pull Aragorn with The Riddermark.<br />
The only thing to remember with this deck is that if you pull 2 copies of the same pipe, to hold onto the other copy until you get past site 3 just incase their playing with a golden hall.<br />
<br />
Apart from that you have the pipes to remove burden&#8217;s + wounds which uses Gandalf&#8217;s and Aragorn&#8217;s pipes (the most important ones), the other pipes are just there for numbers.<br />
<br />
Take an archery wounds as burdens if you can and then remove them later.<br />
The Trust Me&#8217;s are there to keep you on top of things during skirmishes.  You don&#8217;t really have to win them, just stay alive &#8211; although you will want to win them if you need to keep up with your opponent should they run ahead.<br />
<br />
Bilbo&#8217;s there to recycle the pipeweed (hence the use of Frodo Old Bilbo&#8217;s Heir) + there&#8217;s 2 fireworks for the same reason.<br />
<br />
I don&#8217;t need to go into detail for the SH side &#8211; its simply a basic moria swarm, but this is the obvious choice as a counterpart for a pipe deck, as you can rummage through you deck at a rate of knots&#8217; thus getting what you need.  There&#8217;s no need to panic about the deck size you will sore through that with no problems.<br />
<br />
Final Word:<br />
This is more of a fun deck to play around with &#8211; it can annoy your opponent with the amount of wounds/burdens you can take.  There&#8217;s no need to remove twilight as you should be able to take on most things using the Trust Me&#8217;s and remember winning skirmishes isn&#8217;t important, you just wanna keep your guys alive.<br />
<br />
Note for Standard Formant:  The only &#8216;X&#8217; list card used in the above deck is Ottar for going through your deck quickly should you need to.  If playing this deck in Standard Format simply change Ottar for Lindenroot &#8211; this will give you another strong companion, with a good special ability VS Isengard &#8211; but more importantly he lets you discard 2 cards during the assignment phase ;-)<br />
<br />
Have Fun ;-) <br />
<br />
<br />
